				 																DRAMA				 																																	 August 9 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Kalyani Natyacharcha Kendra presents Khowabnama (The Dream Narrative), based on Akhtaruzzaman Elias novel. Direction: Kishore Sengupta.				 																																	 August 10 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Chetana presents Nirnay. Direction: Arun Mukhopadhyay.				 																																	 August 12 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6.30 pm: Nabamayukh Natya Sangstha presents Bhadreswarir Galpo. Direction and acting: Rishi Mukherjee.				 																																	 August 12 at Academy of Fine Arts; 6.30 pm: Nandikar presents Sojon Badiyar Ghaat. Direction: Goutam Halder.				 																																	 August 13 at Gyan Manch; 6.30 pm: Rangakarmee presents Badnam Manto. Direction: Usha Ganguli.				 																																	 August 14 at Girish Mancha; 6.30 pm: Bohurupee presents its latest production, Nishiddha Thikana. Performing director: Debesh Roychowdhury.				 																																	 August 15 at Bharatiyam, Salt Lake; 6.30 pm: Rangakarmee presents Court Martial. Direction: Usha Ganguli.				 																 Art				 																																	 August 9 - 15 at Academy of Fine Arts, New-South Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: A group exhibition of painting, sculpture and collage by Painter 04. Participating artists: Shyamasis Ghosh, Atin Mitra, Sankar Halder, Munmun Das, Rajesh Prasad Srivastava, Anindya Mukherjee, Chandan Das and Sivajyoti Dasgupta.				 																																	 Till August 10 at names-AN.art (Gallery for Contemporary Art), 207A Rashbehari Avenue, near Bharat Sevasram Sangha/Bijon Setu; 3 pm - 7 pm: Paintings by Sekhar Kar.				 																																	 Till August 20 at Genesis Art Gallery, 8B Middleton Street; 2 pm - 7 pm: Habitat Foundation presents an exhibition of paintings by The Ash Family  Gobardhan Ash, Nirban Ash, Deborshi Ash, Jyotirmoy Ash and Chinmoy Ash.				 																																	 August 10 - 14 at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture; 2 pm - 8 pm: Paintings by Sudatta Basu Roy Chowdhury, Tutu Sarkar, Debika Mukherjee (Chattaraj), Dipak Kundu, Barun Roy and Utpal Naskar.				 																																	 Till September 5 at Idiyas Gallery, 15 Dover Road; 10.30 am - 7.30 pm: An exhibition of paintings and sculptures by a group of renowned artists, including Ramananda Bandyopadhyay, Subroto Saha, Prokash Karmakar, Paritosh Sen, Sekhar Kar, Shyamal Sen, Debu De, Sailen Ghosh and Utpal Dasgupta.				 																performing arts				 																																	 August 13 at Bharatiyam, IB-201 Salt Lake; 6.30 pm: A programme of folk music featuring Nikhil Gayen and his group, Subal Das Bairagya Bahurupi, and the use of folk musical instruments like dotara, dhol, patar banshi, mridanga and matir hnari.				 																																	 August 14 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6.30 pm: On its ninth anniversary, Samskritiki Shreyaskar will stage its premier show of Tagores Tasher Desh, a joint venture by Rani Karnaa with her disciples and associated artistes.				 																																	 August 14 at Sujata Sadan; 5.30 pm: Saveri presents an evening of classical music featuring Vidisha Mukherjee (vocal), Chandralekha Banerjee (light classical vocal) and Shyamal Chatterjee (sitar).				 																WORKSHOP				 																																	 August 9 - 20 at Coriolis, 62 Ballygunge Circular Road; 3 pm - 5 pm: Pottery workshop. Details at / 9831060710.				 																																	 August 9 onwards at 6 National Library Avenue: The Creative Arts begins two-month workshops (for children and adults) on Theatre (by Ramanjit) and Monsoon Spalsh (on fine arts by Samit Dey). Details at 23213225.				 																																	 August 10 onwards at Womens Sahayog, 19B Jawaharlal Nehru Road, 1st floor; 11 am - 3 pm: A three-day workshop on counselling, The Theory and Practice of Counselling, covering various aspects of counselling and therapy including marriage and family counselling, group counselling. psycho-analytic approach, rational, emotive and behavior therapy, etc. To be conducted by Dr Rinita Mazumdar, professor of womens studies, University of New Mexico, and counsellor at Albuquerque Womens Resource Center. Details at .				 																PHOTOGRAPHS				 																																	 Till August 12 at Sri Aurobindo Institute of Culture, 3 Regent Park; 4 pm - 7 pm: An exhibition of photographs taken by Alain Dainelou, an eminent photographer from France. Organised jointly with Alliance Francaise de Calcutta.				 																																	 August 13 - 19 (except August 15) at Gorky Sadan; 4 pm - 7 pm: To celebrate the return of the Olympic Games to Greece, the cultural department of the Russian Federation Consulate General in Calcutta presents Glimpses of Greece  an exhibition of photographs by Mala Mukerjee. Inauguration on August 13 at 6 pm.				 																FILM SHOW				 																																	 August 10 at Nandan-II; 6 pm: Cine Central, Calcutta organises a special screening of Genesis, directed by Mrinal Sen to mark the release of his memoir, Always Being Born.				 																TALK				 																																	 August 9 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Vivekananda Hall; 6.15 pm: Swami Puranananda will speak in Bengali on Adhyatma Ramayana.				 																																	 August 10 at CMA Auditorium, 1 Shakespeare Sarani, 1st floor (rear side); 5.45 pm: The CMA-Patton Tuesday Talkshoppe: Mr Aniruddha Ray, director, Eveready Industries India Ltd, to speak on Competitiveness.				 																SEMINAR				 																																	 August 9 at British Council; 7 pm: A panel discussion on Questioning Borders: Migratory Writers. Speakers: Sushila Nasta, David Dabydeen, Mini Krishnan and Amit Chaudhuri. Moderator: Dr Sanjukta Dasgupta.				 																																	 August 10 at Taj Bengal; 11 am: Tata Pipes hosts a seminar on Rain Water Harvesting. The seminar will be presented by the Centre for Science amp; Environment, New Delhi.				 																																	 August 10 at Bangla Academy Sabhaghar; 6 pm: Gobardanga Naksha hosts a seminar on Marketing of Theatre. Speakers: Usha Ganguli, Niranjan Goswami, Shyamanand Jalan and Rudraprasad Sengupta. Co-ordinator: Basudeb Hui.				 																																	 August 14 at Bangla Academy Sabhaghar; 6 pm: Kalyani Natyacharcha Kendra hosts a seminar on Contemporary Theatres in the Context of Socio-Political Scenario.				 																BOOKS				 																																	 August 9 at Apeejay House, 1st floor, Sangam Hall, 15 Park Street; 7 pm: Oxford Bookstore and Stellar Publishers present the launch of Always Being Born by Mrinal Sen. Chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee will release the memoir.				 																																	 Till August 16 at Oxford Bookstore, Park Street: A special exhibition on Oxford University Press titles. Categories: Non-fiction, dictionaries, anthology, sociology and economics.				 																EXHIBITION				 																																	 Till August 21 at Mrignayani, Dakshinapan, Dhakuria: Madhya Pradesh Laghu Udyog Nigam Ltd organises Karigar-Hat, an exhibition and live demonstration of traditional handloom and handicraft products of MP by national award wining craftsmen.				 																IN MEMORIAM				 																																	 August 11 at Madhusudan Mancha; 5.30 pm: Pradip Ghosh will release a CD, titled Shraddhanjali (in memory of celebrated musician Batuk Nandy), in which Nilanjan Nandy has sung eight Tagore songs along Samir Dasguptas recitation and Krishna Dasguptas instrumental music. Also, Lok-Krishti will stage its on-going play, Its a Game (direction: Phalguni Chatterjee).
